  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Love barter, education for 150 Colombian children</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Laudes Infantis plans to adequate three communitary centers and offer school kits; as well as library spaces, homework support, art, culture, psychosocial assessment for 150 children (and their families) in vulnerable or forced displacement conditions in the southern periphery of Bogota. In order to accomplish this, parents must generate co-responsibility with the services received with love barters (commitment to build strong affective bonds in the family).</narrative>
  </description>
